  <title>Vectors Introduction</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      Vectors come into play whenever we care more than just about the magnitude of a quantity.  "Direction" can mean a lot more than the pointing of an arrow, by the way.  But in general, having both direction/orientation and a magnitude gives us much more flexibility in applying mathematics in the real world.  Very few things are represented accurately as just "scalars" or just plain numbers without any other properties.
    </p>
